    What is difference between tag and element?
    a tag is a keyword surrounded by angle brackets (< >). It is used to define the start and end of an element. An element is a piece of content on a web page, such as a heading, paragraph, or image. The <p> tag is the start tag, and the </p> tag is the end tag.30 Aug 2023

    Is HTML a tag or element?
    The <html> element is the root element and it defines the whole HTML document. It has a start tag <html> and an end tag </html> . The <body> element defines the document's body. It has a start tag <body> and an end tag </body> .
